President Muhammadu Buhari, on Tuesday, ordered the rejig of operational strategies of Nigeria’s security network. The President said this will effectively counter the security situation across the country. This was made known by Major General Babagana Mungono, rtd, National Security Adviser (NSA), after a National Security Council meeting held at the State House. He also told State House Correspondents that the government was working on a solution to the security crisis in some parts of the country. According to him, the Minister of Defense, Major General Bashir Salihi Magashi (Rtd), was “working on something.” The NSA further revealed that the council noted that proliferation of drugs was driving insecurity in the country. Details later…